WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.960
this very familiar passage of scripture,

00:00:02.960 --> 00:00:05.239
lengthy passage of scripture,

00:00:05.239 --> 00:00:07.679
and be looking here this evening.

00:00:07.679 --> 00:00:12.359
In fact, this evening will be part one of a lesson.

00:00:12.359 --> 00:00:14.520
We'll have three parts

00:00:14.520 --> 00:00:17.020
to this particular thought this evening.

00:00:17.020 --> 00:00:18.840
And as you're turning your Bible,

00:00:18.840 --> 00:00:20.360
we know that just recently

00:00:20.360 --> 00:00:23.479
we've turned a page in our calendars.

00:00:23.479 --> 00:00:27.399
And I believe that as you begin to think about a new year,

00:00:27.399 --> 00:00:30.479
this is the first Wednesday of 2026,

00:00:30.479 --> 00:00:31.920
and that's hard to believe.

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:33.779
We know that we already had our first Sunday.

00:00:33.779 --> 00:00:36.520
We've introduced our theme and all of those things.

00:00:36.520 --> 00:00:38.759
But I believe that as you enter into a new year,

00:00:38.759 --> 00:00:41.159
that oftentimes we take an opportunity

00:00:41.159 --> 00:00:43.020
to look back at the previous year

00:00:43.020 --> 00:00:44.740
and what was accomplished

00:00:44.740 --> 00:00:46.639
and what we've learned and so on and so forth.

00:00:46.639 --> 00:00:50.819
But we also take time to look forward into the next year.

00:00:50.819 --> 00:00:54.259
And as we begin to do that and look into that next year,

00:00:54.259 --> 00:00:57.639
sometimes, many times, in fact, folks will set goals

00:00:57.639 --> 00:01:00.040
and they'll have certain aspirations

00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:01.299
that they set out to do.

00:01:01.299 --> 00:01:04.419
And sometimes people notate things

00:01:04.419 --> 00:01:06.620
that they want to accomplish,

00:01:06.620 --> 00:01:08.540
places that they wanna go,

00:01:08.540 --> 00:01:09.980
sites that they wanna see.

00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:11.379
And they do these kind of things.

00:01:11.379 --> 00:01:14.959
And I think for me personally,

00:01:14.959 --> 00:01:16.019
it's almost something

00:01:16.019 --> 00:01:18.699
that's just become part of our culture,

00:01:18.699 --> 00:01:20.500
that when you change that calendar

00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:22.900
from December 31st to January 1st,

00:01:22.900 --> 00:01:25.660
you just kinda, it's all around us so many things.

00:01:25.660 --> 00:01:28.180
But it does give us an opportunity

00:01:28.180 --> 00:01:30.500
to really acknowledge some things

00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:31.459
that have been accomplished,

00:01:31.459 --> 00:01:33.519
but also have a perspective

00:01:33.519 --> 00:01:36.019
with regard to what the next year holds.

00:01:36.019 --> 00:01:37.980
As we begin to think about that personally

00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:39.620
and then also for our church,

00:01:39.620 --> 00:01:43.260
something is just really upon my heart

00:01:43.260 --> 00:01:45.059
that I wanna share with you.

00:01:45.059 --> 00:01:46.919
And as I think about my own life

00:01:46.919 --> 00:01:48.419
and then think about our church,

00:01:48.419 --> 00:01:49.860
I would say this,

00:01:49.860 --> 00:01:52.540
I long to see God work.

00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:56.300
I long to see God work in a definite

00:01:56.300 --> 00:01:58.059
and in a mighty way.

00:01:58.059 --> 00:02:02.620
I wanna see God do what we cannot do.

00:02:02.620 --> 00:02:03.940
Amen, I don't wanna just see

00:02:03.940 --> 00:02:07.339
what we can accomplish as a group of individuals.

00:02:07.339 --> 00:02:09.619
I wanna see what God can do.

00:02:09.619 --> 00:02:11.580
And I know that our God is able

00:02:11.580 --> 00:02:13.660
to do exceeding abundantly above

00:02:13.660 --> 00:02:15.139
all that we ask or think.

00:02:15.139 --> 00:02:17.220
And our God is the one that said,

00:02:17.220 --> 00:02:18.339
let there be light.

00:02:18.339 --> 00:02:21.660
Our God is the one that the Bible simply says,

00:02:21.660 --> 00:02:23.740
and he made the stars also

00:02:23.740 --> 00:02:26.440
and begin to think about the God that we know,

00:02:26.440 --> 00:02:27.740
the God that we serve.

00:02:27.740 --> 00:02:29.899
And I think about how he saved my soul.

00:02:29.899 --> 00:02:30.899
And I think about the things

00:02:30.899 --> 00:02:32.259
that he's done in my life.

00:02:32.259 --> 00:02:35.419
And I long to see him work.

00:02:35.419 --> 00:02:37.940
And I begin to think about this longing

00:02:37.940 --> 00:02:39.740
and I've titled the message this evening,

00:02:39.740 --> 00:02:40.660
if you're taking notes,

00:02:40.660 --> 00:02:43.179
a longing to see God work.

00:02:43.179 --> 00:02:45.020
It'll be part one this evening.

00:02:45.020 --> 00:02:46.100
And for tonight,

00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:47.720
