00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:49.239
It's proper, it's appropriate for us.

00:05:49.239 --> 00:05:50.880
It's appropriate for the Psalmist

00:05:50.880 --> 00:05:53.339
to come before the throne room of God,

00:05:53.339 --> 00:05:54.720
to come before the Lord and say,

00:05:54.720 --> 00:05:57.720
"'Lord, it's time for thee to work.'"

00:05:57.720 --> 00:06:01.920
This request reveals to us the heart of the Psalmist

00:06:01.920 --> 00:06:05.279
and the desire, the longing in the heart of the Psalmist

00:06:05.279 --> 00:06:09.119
to see God do what only God can do.

00:06:09.119 --> 00:06:11.399
And I would say to you this evening

00:06:11.399 --> 00:06:16.399
that it's important that we come to God.

00:06:16.559 --> 00:06:20.480
It's appropriate, it's proper that we would come to God

00:06:20.480 --> 00:06:22.920
and beg God to do something.

00:06:23.899 --> 00:06:27.239
I've said this before, we need God.

00:06:27.239 --> 00:06:28.559
We need God.

00:06:28.559 --> 00:06:31.880
It's not enough to see what our flesh can do.

00:06:31.880 --> 00:06:35.179
It's not enough to see what collectively or corporately

00:06:35.179 --> 00:06:36.559
